<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[35801]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[The Sagrada Família will be surrounded by the 'Milla']]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Sport.</strong> On Sunday 27 April nearly 2,000 athletes will take part in the 30th Milla Sagrada Família-Gran Premi Gaudí SPORT.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>One of the best urban miles is coming to Barcelona next Sunday, 27 April, courtesy of the Claror Foundation: the <em>Milla Sagrada Família-Gran Premi Gaudí SPORT</em>. The 2,000 athletes taking part will run 1,609 metres by doing one and a half laps of the &quot;Illa Gaudí&quot; in series.</p>
<p>The run will be accompanied by other fun activities as part of the neighbourhood&#8217;s <em>festa major</em>. Recreational activities in the form of a <em>gimcana</em>, a kind of treasure hunt that all the family can enjoy, have been organised from ten till one. And the end of the mile series will signal the start of an outdoor <em>zumba</em>  master class with live 80s rock music.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
